sentences: Achille Millien (4 September 1838 – 12 January 1927) was a French poet and folklorist.
As soon as 1877, Millien began the systematic collection of folk tales, legends and folk songs of the Nivernais region.
In 1896, he established the Revue du Nivernais, a monthly publication which appeared until 1910.
